==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indirectness
<hw>In`di*rect"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being indirect; obliquity; deviousness; crookedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deviation from an upright or straightforward course;
unfairness; dishonesty.</def> <rj><au>W. Montagu.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indiretin</ent>⟦br⟧
